{
  "texts": [
    "However, this process is not straightforward.",
    "For a T3 robot, the word \"cat\" gains meaning through direct interaction with cats (DSG) and/or grounded featurebased descriptions from other grounded entities (IVG).",
    "The GPT component, on the other hand, 'understands' \"cat\" as a cluster of linguistic patterns and information without direct experiential grounding.",
    "The GPT's linguistic data on \"cats\" includes descriptions, characteristics, and contexts, but lacks experiential grounding.",
    "This ungrounded information can't be directly \"taught\" to the T3 component in the same way a human would learn about cats because the T3's understanding is fundamentally experiential."
  ]
}